<h1>Problem 1636 - 2021 IMOSL, C2</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(n\ge 3\) be a fixed integer. There are \(m\ge n+1\) beads on a circular necklace. You wish to paint the beads using \(n\) colors, such that among any \(n+1\) consecutive beads every color appears at least once. Find the largest value of \(m\) for which this task is <i>not</i> possible.</p>
